      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bush's Road Out of the Balkans</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>William S Shogren letter contends Gov George W Bush's avowed aim to pull military out of Balkans is ignorant (Oct 21 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>George W. Bush's avowed aim to pull the military out of the Balkans and to reduce peacekeeping and nation-building efforts elsewhere so that the troops are ready for a major war is ignorant (front page, Oct. 21).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>George W. Bush's avowed aim to pull the military out of the Balkans and to reduce peacekeeping and nation-building efforts elsewhere so that the troops are ready for a major war is ignorant (front page, Oct. 21).</p>
        <p>We have avoided a major war because of these military commitments. They are honorable, they are productive, and they have saved countless lives. To cancel them now is foolishness.</p>
        <p>WILLIAM S. SHOGREN  Green Bay, Wis., Oct. 21, 2000</p>
      </block>
